cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI 

This paper deals with training deep neural networks with sparse prediction targets, which is a common problem in natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of word embeddings, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and the potential application to image recognition, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
